UILanguageTooltip.message: The language used by the extension when displaying text.

TheExtensionIsStillLoading.message: The extension is still loading and cannot load the Debug Log yet.

SettingNotControllable.message: The extension cannot control this setting.

SettingControlledByOther.message: This setting is being controlled by another extension.

AllowExtensionNotificationsTooltip.message: Allow the extension to create a desktop notification when something important happens. Not recommended to disable.

FingerprintProtectionTooltip.message: Protect against browser fingerprinting by providing generic information about your computer and preventing access to certain browser APIs.

FingerprintProtectionDisclaimer.message: This setting can provide extra privacy and security but may break certain websites and cause the browser to behave differently than expected. A full list of modifications can be found here:

FingerprintProtectionInstructions.message: This feature is recommended but some users may find it inconvenient. Please choose to either enable or disable Fingerprint Protection:

FingerprintProtectionAfterword.message: This setting can also be changed from the "Extension Settings" panel after logging into the extension.

TrackingProtectionTooltip.message: Blocks requests made to domains that are known to engage in cross-site tracking of users.

BlockHyperlinkAuditingTooltip.message: Disable hyperlink auditing, a recent HTML feature designed for notifying trackers and analytic services when you click on a link.

DebugModeTooltip.message: Write messages to the debug log. Press the 'ctrl' key followed by the 'd' key to show the debug log.

DarkThemeTooltip.message: Enable a darker theme for the extension to use in low light conditions

AlwaysActiveTooltip.message: Cause settings to always remain active, regardless of whether proxy is connected or not

LogMeOutOnClose.message: Log me out on browser close

LogMeOutOnCloseTooltip.message: After reopening the browser you will not be logged back in automatically

LogMeOutOnCloseDisabled.message: This setting cannot be controlled while credentials are not being remembered (login screen)

PersistentSettingsDisclaimer.message: Enabled settings are now always active whether you are connected to a region or not, with the exception of PIA MACE™ which is only active when you are connected to a region.

NetworkError.message: Login request failed due to a network error. Please try again.

OfflineError.message: Login request failed because you appear to be offline. Please check if you are connected to the internet.

TimeoutError.message: Login request timed out after %{seconds} seconds. Please try again.

AbortError.message: Login request was aborted by the browser. Please try again.

UnexpectedServerResponse.message: Login request returned an unexpected server response (%{statusLine})

TooManyRequestsError.message: Too many failed login attempts. Try again later.

SettingsWarning.message: These settings are not in effect. They come into effect while you are connected to a region.

SettingsWarningConnected.message: These settings are in effect. They will be restored to %{browser}'s default settings when you disconnect from %{region}.

BypassWarning.message: Requests made to websites found on the Bypass List use a direct connection that is not protected by Private Internet Access™.

MaceTooltip.message: PIA MACE™ helps protect your privacy and security by blocking malicious content, trackers and ads. Only active when connected to a region

WebRTCTooltip.message: Block %{browser} from revealing your public and private IP addresses when WebRTC is being used. Not recommended to disable.

AdobeFlashTooltip.message: Block %{browser} from running Adobe Flash. Adobe Flash can be used to reveal your public IP address. Not recommended to disable.

HttpsUpgradeTooltip.message: Automatically converts supported websites or links using an unencrypted connection (HTTP) to a more secure HTTPS connection before leaving your browser. Made possible because of HTTPS Everywhere and the EFF.

BlockUTMTooltip.message: Remove Urchin Tracking Model(UTM) parameters from URLs you click on. UTM parameters are used to track information about your visit to a website.

BlockFBCLIDTooltip.message: Remove Facebook FBCLID parameters from outgoing links in Facebook. FBCLID parameters are used to track information about your visit to a website

BypassInstructions.message: to bypass all subdomains for a website.

BlockNetworkPredictionTooltip.message: Disable %{browser} from using a network prediction service that pre-resolves DNS queries and pre-fetches webpages from the content found on a page you visit.

BlockSafeBrowsingTooltip.message: Disable %{browser} from making direct connections to a network service that has privacy concerns around keeping logs. PIA Mace™ mitigates the risk in disabling this service.

BlockAutofillTooltip.message: Disable %{browser} from automatically filling in forms. This could leak personal data via hidden form fields.

BlockAutofillCreditCardTooltip.message: Disable %{browser} from automatically filling in credit card information. This could leak personal data via hidden form fields.

BlockAutofillAddressTooltip.message: Disable %{browser} from automatically filling addresses and other form data. This could leak personal data via hidden form fields.

BlockLocationAccessTooltip.message: Block websites from accessing information about your physical location.

BlockHTTPRefererTooltip.message: Disable %{browser} from sending the address of the current webpage to another webpage when following a link.

BlockThirdpartycookiesTooltip.message: Disable %{browser} from accepting cookies from third party websites. Third party cookies can be used to track your visit to a website by a third party website or web service.

BlockCameraAccessTooltip.message: Block websites from accessing your computer's camera.

BlockMicrophoneAccessTooltip.message: Block websites from accessing your computer's microphone.

UseRegionLocaleTooltip.message: The default locale and language settings of your browser are kept private by replacing them with the locale and language settings of the current region.

ImportFileMessage.message: Please select an exported Bypass Rules file (ex. bypass-rules.json)

InvalidImportFileStructure.message: File cannot be read, please select a valid file

CannotUsePIAMessage.message: Private Internet Access cannot be used because another extension is controlling your browsers proxy settings.

UpgradeBrowserMessage.message: Private Internet Access cannot be used because your version of %{browser} is outdated. Please upgrade %{browser} to its latest version.

AuthFailMessage.message:
If you recently changed your password on the Private Internet Access website then re-authenticating with the extension might fix this error.

For help and support, contact our support team.

ConnectionFailMessage.message: You might have lost connectivity to the internet, your connection might have been temporarily interrupted, or the Private Internet Access server you are connecting to might have connectivity issues.

PrivateBrowsingChangeLead.message: Firefox has recently changed the way addons handle proxy connections. Allowing the addon to run in Private Windows is now required for proxy settings to be updated.

PrivateBrowsingChangeDirections.message: Please visit the URL below to view your addons page. Then click on the "Private Internet Access" addon to modify its settings. From here, change the "Run in Private Windows" setting to "Allow".
